@dependabot This bump failed CI because Expo SDK ~55.0.28 only supports `@react-native-community/datetimepicker@8.6.0` — `expo-doctor`'s package-compatibility check flags 9.1.0 as a major-version mismatch (see the "Run Expo Doctor" step in the failed run). This isn't a lockfile/peer-dep quirk; Expo just hasn't added the 9.x line to its SDK 55 compatibility table yet.

Fix: reverted `app/package.json` and `app/package-lock.json` back to `8.6.0` (the version `expo-doctor` expects), regenerated the lockfile via `npm install`, and confirmed the version now matches what CI checks for.

Maintainer: this PR now effectively re-pins the existing version rather than upgrading. It's safe to close/ignore this bump until Expo SDK adds support for datetimepicker 9.x — consider adding it to `expo.install.exclude` if Dependabot keeps retrying it in the meantime.

@app/dependabot The automated review is right that this bump is a no-op at best: \`@grpc/grpc-js\` and \`@grpc/proto-loader\` both pin \`protobufjs\` to \`^7.x\`, so they can't resolve to \`8.7.1\`. Bumping the root dependency didn't move anything running to 8.x — it just added an unused top-level 8.7.1 copy and forced npm to nest two extra deduped-away 7.6.5 copies under the grpc packages instead of one shared copy.

Fix: reverted \`app/package.json\`'s \`protobufjs\` to \`^7.6.5\` and regenerated \`app/package-lock.json\` (\`npm ci\` verified clean, single deduped \`protobufjs@7.6.5\` entry restored, no nested duplicates).

Maintainer: worth adding a dependabot ignore rule for protobufjs major versions (as the reviewer suggested) so this doesn't keep recurring until grpc-js/proto-loader accept 8.x.

@dependabot This bump broke CI lint: ESLint 10 removed the deprecated `context.getFilename()` method, but the bundled `eslint-plugin-react@7.37.5` (via `eslint-config-next@16.2.3`) still calls it when resolving `settings.react.version: "detect"`, so every lint run crashed with `TypeError: contextOrFilename.getFilename is not a function`. `eslint-plugin-react` has no newer release that fixes this yet (7.37.5 is latest, peer range still `^9.7` max), and bumping `eslint-config-next` doesn't help since it still pulls `eslint-plugin-react@^7.37.0`.

Fix: in `website/eslint.config.mjs`, override `settings.react.version` to the installed React version (`19.2.4`) instead of relying on `"detect"`, which skips the crashing auto-detect code path entirely. Verified `npm run lint` and `npm run build` both pass locally.

Worth checking in on when `eslint-plugin-react` ships ESLint 10 support — at that point the explicit version override can likely be removed again, though it's harmless to leave in place either way.

**Claude finished @yanukadeneth99's task in 5m 5s** —— [View job](https://github.com/yanukadeneth99/Cue-Clock/actions/runs/29653809718)

---
### Review blockers addressed — pushed to this PR

All four blockers from the rejection are fixed. `npm run lint` + `npm run build` both pass.

- [x] **#1 Premature reveal** — the root cause was correct: `document.fonts.check()` returns `true` before the Material Symbols `@font-face` is even registered (system fallback), so icons revealed while still fallback text. The reveal now gates on **both** conditions — the face is *registered* in `document.fonts` **and** `check()` reports it loaded:
  ```js
  function ready() {
    var has = false;
    document.fonts.forEach(function (f) {
      if (f.family.indexOf('Material Symbols') > -1) has = true;
    });
    return has && document.fonts.check(F);
  }
  ```
  Before the remote stylesheet parses, no matching face exists → `ready()` is `false` → the box stays empty. It can only reveal once the real glyph font is genuinely available. A 60s cap still guarantees icons can't stay hidden forever if the font fails.
- [x] **#3 No-JS regression** — the icon `opacity: 0` is now behind `html.js`; the box-lock (`width`/`height`/`overflow`) stays unconditional. No-JS visitors keep a stable layout **and** still get icons once the font loads, instead of permanently blank boxes.
- [x] **#4 GSAP fragility** — added a 10s `gsap-safety` timer; the guard is now `html.js:not(.gsap-safety) …`, so if `useGSAP` ever throws before writing inline opacity, the hero reveals instead of staying stuck at `opacity: 0`. (Kept the hero fix in-scope because you reported that flash directly as a bug in this PR.)
- [x] **#2 Comment length** — trimmed both the `globals.css` icon/hero blocks and the `layout.tsx` head-script comment to short, plain-language notes per the CLAUDE.md non-negotiable.

**Files:** `website/src/app/globals.css`, `website/src/app/layout.tsx` (net −13 lines).

---

**One honest caveat:** I can't drive a real Slow-4G throttle from here, so I verified this by reasoning about the Font Loading API semantics + build/lint, not by re-watching the timeline on a throttled profile. The logic is now provably gated on the face being registered, which is the specific gap the previous attempts missed — but please do a final throttled check before merging.

**Still on the table (larger, cleaner):** swapping the ~21 Material Symbols usages to inline SVGs would delete the remote-font dependency, the reveal script, and all of this timing logic at once — the fully offline-first path. I kept it as a separate follow-up rather than bundle a ~31-icon rewrite into this PR, but happy to do it if you'd prefer that direction.
